1
00:00:02,734 --> 00:00:06,043
We’re all unique.

2
00:00:06,289 --> 00:00:12,274
Sometimes people who subscribe
to democracy are very proud

3
00:00:12,274 --> 00:00:17,535
of the Declaration of Independence 
in America.

4
00:00:17,535 --> 00:00:20,248
Especially Americans, but even 
other people, they’ll say,

5
00:00:20,248 --> 00:00:23,550
“There it says, 
Thomas Jefferson wrote,

6
00:00:23,550 --> 00:00:25,706
‘All men are created equal.’”

7
00:00:25,767 --> 00:00:28,189
[All Beings are Eternally Unique]

8
00:00:28,914 --> 00:00:31,252
Then first question:
“And women?”

9
00:00:31,252 --> 00:00:34,700
Women didn’t have equal rights
when he wrote that.

10
00:00:34,700 --> 00:00:37,583
And what to speak 
of people of colour,

11
00:00:37,583 --> 00:00:39,852
they weren’t considered …

12
00:00:39,852 --> 00:00:42,591
They weren’t as enlightened
as they appeared to be,

13
00:00:42,591 --> 00:00:46,942
the so-called
“enlightenment thinkers”.

14
00:00:47,727 --> 00:00:51,627
To rephrase that we can say,

15
00:00:51,627 --> 00:00:56,695
“All beings are eternally unique.”

16
00:00:56,695 --> 00:00:59,540
Because that didn’t include 
our friends the animals

17
00:00:59,540 --> 00:01:00,938
and so many others.

18
00:01:00,938 --> 00:01:03,066
So rather we can restate that as,

19
00:01:03,066 --> 00:01:10,514
“All beings are eternally unique”.
 

20
00:01:12,222 --> 00:01:16,511
So, we have so much variegatedness 
in the human position,

21
00:01:16,511 --> 00:01:20,365
in the animal position,
in all of the species.

22
00:01:20,365 --> 00:01:22,349
And as I stated 
at the beginning,

23
00:01:22,349 --> 00:01:27,533
“The body is the biological expression
of the soul’s delusion.”

24
00:01:27,533 --> 00:01:32,825
So no two are identical, actually, 
and in that sense not equal.

25
00:01:32,825 --> 00:01:34,329
They’re all unique.

26
00:01:34,329 --> 00:01:38,357
There are similarities,
but all unique.

27
00:01:38,357 --> 00:01:40,716
So, we look the way we do …

28
00:01:40,716 --> 00:01:43,872
You could say this,
if you’re following the theme

29
00:01:43,872 --> 00:01:46,170
of what we’re discussing
this evening,

30
00:01:46,170 --> 00:01:49,236
is that the way 
we look at present

31
00:01:49,236 --> 00:01:55,580
is a perverted reflection 
of our spiritual features.

32
00:01:57,590 --> 00:02:04,403
We have unique spiritual forms
and features called swarūp,

33
00:02:04,564 --> 00:02:09,816
but the swarūp at present 
is covered by layers of ego,

34
00:02:09,816 --> 00:02:11,645
in Guru Mahārāj’s words:

35
00:02:11,645 --> 00:02:16,318
acquired prejudice, 
acquired tendencies.

36
00:02:16,331 --> 00:02:20,642
It’s being pervertedly expressed
into this plane.

37
00:02:20,642 --> 00:02:25,771
Our loving propensity 
towards Kṛṣṇa is being expressed

38
00:02:25,771 --> 00:02:31,188
as an exploiting tendency 
towards matter in the mundane,

39
00:02:31,188 --> 00:02:35,135
and we’ve taken on 
these varieties of forms

40
00:02:35,353 --> 00:02:37,265
that are all unique,

41
00:02:37,265 --> 00:02:39,607
but they’re perverted reflections 
of the original.

42
00:02:39,607 --> 00:02:41,563
That swarūp 
covered by layers of ego,

43
00:02:41,563 --> 00:02:46,244
acquired prejudice, acquired tendency,
mind, mental body,

44
00:02:46,244 --> 00:02:52,088
or intellectual body, mental body, 
physical body,

45
00:02:53,072 --> 00:03:01,945
but still it’s different, unique;
but it’s not the pure expression.

46
00:03:01,950 --> 00:03:04,814
When we’re enriched
with dedicating tendency,

47
00:03:04,814 --> 00:03:09,849
when we withdraw from
the plane of exploitation

48
00:03:09,849 --> 00:03:16,532
and are reconfigured as 
dedicating units, servitors,

49
00:03:16,532 --> 00:03:23,507
then, gradually this body,

50
00:03:23,507 --> 00:03:28,368
which is constructed upon 
exploiting tendencies,

51
00:03:28,368 --> 00:03:31,128
starts to dissolve.

52
00:03:31,128 --> 00:03:37,657
And the swarūp, which is
the spiritual form expression

53
00:03:37,657 --> 00:03:41,315
of dedicating tendency, 
starts to manifest.

